{"nodes":[{"pos":[12,49],"content":"Compiler Error C3162 | Microsoft Docs","needQuote":false,"needEscape":true,"nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error C3162 | Microsoft Docs","pos":[0,37]}]},{"content":"Compiler Error C3162","pos":[597,617]},{"content":"'type' : a reference type which has a destructor cannot be used as the type of static data member 'member'","pos":[618,724]},{"content":"The common language runtime cannot know when to run a user-defined destructor when the class also contains static member function.","pos":[731,861]},{"content":"A destructor will never be run unless the object is deleted explicitly.","pos":[868,939]},{"content":"For more information, see,","pos":[946,972]},{"content":"/clr (Common Language Runtime Compilation)","pos":[983,1025]},{"content":"Common Visual C++ 64-bit Migration Issues","pos":[1103,1144]},{"content":"Example","pos":[1212,1219]},{"content":"The following sample generates C3162.","pos":[1223,1260]}],"content":"---\ntitle: \"Compiler Error C3162 | Microsoft Docs\"\nms.custom: \"\"\nms.date: \"11/04/2016\"\nms.reviewer: \"\"\nms.suite: \"\"\nms.technology: \n  - \"devlang-cpp\"\nms.tgt_pltfrm: \"\"\nms.topic: \"error-reference\"\nf1_keywords: \n  - \"C3162\"\ndev_langs: \n  - \"C++\"\nhelpviewer_keywords: \n  - \"C3162\"\nms.assetid: 0d4c4a24-1456-4191-b7d8-c38cb7b17c32\ncaps.latest.revision: 4\nauthor: \"corob-msft\"\nms.author: \"corob\"\nmanager: \"ghogen\"\ntranslation.priority.ht: \n  - \"cs-cz\"\n  - \"de-de\"\n  - \"es-es\"\n  - \"fr-fr\"\n  - \"it-it\"\n  - \"ja-jp\"\n  - \"ko-kr\"\n  - \"pl-pl\"\n  - \"pt-br\"\n  - \"ru-ru\"\n  - \"tr-tr\"\n  - \"zh-cn\"\n  - \"zh-tw\"\n---\n# Compiler Error C3162\n'type' : a reference type which has a destructor cannot be used as the type of static data member 'member'  \n  \n The common language runtime cannot know when to run a user-defined destructor when the class also contains static member function.  \n  \n A destructor will never be run unless the object is deleted explicitly.  \n  \n For more information, see,  \n  \n-   [/clr (Common Language Runtime Compilation)](../../build/reference/clr-common-language-runtime-compilation.md)  \n  \n-   [Common Visual C++ 64-bit Migration Issues](../../build/common-visual-cpp-64-bit-migration-issues.md)  \n  \n## Example  \n The following sample generates C3162.  \n  \n```  \n// C3162.cpp  \n// compile with: /clr /c  \nref struct A {  \n   ~A() { System::Console::WriteLine(\"in destructor\"); }  \n   static A i;   // C3162  \n   static A^ a = gcnew A;   // OK  \n};  \n  \nint main() {  \n   A ^ a = gcnew A;  \n   delete a;  \n}  \n```"}